[SN]TITLE[SN]
Avalanche sweeps climber over crags in Glen Spean

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A climber has been swept about 300m over crags after triggering an avalanche in the west Highlands.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The accident happened on Creag Meagaidh, to the north of Glen Spean.
The climber was taken off the mountain by a coastguard rescue helicopter and transferred to Belford Hospital in Fort William.
The climber's companion was able to walk away from the area and was later assisted by members of the Lochaber Mountain Rescue Team.
It is understood the climber's injuries are not significant.
